          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-04 09:50:12" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to buy out the time) to take full advantage of any opportunity</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to make good use of every opportunity</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to take advantage of every chance</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The implication of this statement in {S:05100400500018} is taking advantage of every opportunity to manifest the reality of one’s faith.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
